{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SurfaceLayerUpdate",
        "description": "Top-layer ice and liquid water mass-rate updates from surface dew, frost, and sublimation, following Oleson et al. (2010, CLM Tech Note Ch. 5) Eqs. 5.150-5.152. Migrated from UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4 src/hydrology.jl:860 (`SurfaceLayerUpdate` @component). Parameterized as observed-only: q_sdew, q_frost, q_subl are inputs (parameters); dw_liq_1, dw_ice_1_frost, dw_ice_1_subl are algebraic outputs that pass each input through (with a sign flip on sublimation). Applies to the top layer of all surfaces (roof, pervious road, impervious road).",
        "tags": [
            "urban_canopy",
            "hydrology",
            "surface_layer",
            "observed-only",
            "clmu"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-06T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "UrbanCanopy.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (mdl-bylo)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Oleson, K. W., et al. (2010). Technical Description of version 4.0 of the Community Land Model (CLM). NCAR Technical Note NCAR/TN-478+STR. Chapter 5, Section 5.4 (Surface Layer Hydrology), Eqs. 5.150-5.152, p. 146."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "SurfaceLayerUpdate": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4f15609f20339d3a7d104de8064544310:src/hydrology.jl:860\nUpstream `SurfaceLayerUpdate` is an MTK `@component` whose three inputs (q_sdew, q_frost, q_subl) are `@parameters` and whose three outputs (dw_liq_1, dw_ice_1_frost, dw_ice_1_subl) are time-indexed `@variables` with algebraic-only equations (no derivatives). The three equations are:\n  • dw_liq_1        ~  q_sdew    (Eq. 5.150 — rate form)\n  • dw_ice_1_frost  ~  q_frost   (Eq. 5.151 — rate form)\n  • dw_ice_1_subl   ~ -q_subl    (Eq. 5.152 — rate form, sublimation removes ice)\nIdentical structure preserved here. The negation in Eq. 5.152 is encoded as multiplication by -1 — the same pattern used by snow_compaction.esm for `C_R1 = -c_3 * ...`.\n\nObservability classification: this component is functionally observed-only — every output is given by a single algebraic equation in terms of the parameters (and the `(t)` time index has no role since there is no derivative). Test scenarios use `time_span: [0, 1]` and sample at t=0 to mirror the convention used by the other observed-only ESM files in this rig (e.g. soil_water_content_calc.esm, snow_melt_no_layers.esm).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-9): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); two of the three equations are pass-through (zero floating-point ops), and the third is a single negation (one IEEE-754 sign flip — exact). Round-off is ~1e-16. 1e-9 leaves comfortable headroom and is well below any plausible physical-discrimination scale on surface mass fluxes (which are typically 1e-7 to 1e-3 kg/(m^2*s) for dew/frost/sublimation in CLMU). Branches where the expected value is exactly zero by construction add `abs: 1e-15` to guard against silent stuck-at-large regressions."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-9
            },
            "variables": {
                "q_sdew": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Surface dew rate (liquid condensation onto the surface)"
                },
                "q_frost": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Frost rate (vapor deposition as ice)"
                },
                "q_subl": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Sublimation rate (ice → vapor; sign-flipped on the ice-mass tendency)"
                },
                "dw_liq_1": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "description": "Rate of change of top-layer liquid water from dew (Oleson Eq. 5.150): dw_liq_1 = q_sdew"
                },
                "dw_ice_1_frost": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "description": "Rate of change of top-layer ice from frost (Oleson Eq. 5.151): dw_ice_1_frost = q_frost"
                },
                "dw_ice_1_subl": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "description": "Rate of change of top-layer ice from sublimation (Oleson Eq. 5.152): dw_ice_1_subl = -q_subl"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "dw_liq_1",
                    "rhs": "q_sdew"
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "dw_ice_1_frost",
                    "rhs": "q_frost"
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "dw_ice_1_subl",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [-1, "q_subl"]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "all_zero",
                    "description": "No surface fluxes (all three rates zero). Each tendency must be exactly zero — the trivial baseline that confirms the equations and the runner do not introduce spurious offsets.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_sdew": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_subl": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "dw_liq_1",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "dew_only",
                    "description": "Surface dew at 1e-5 kg/(m^2*s) (a typical CLMU early-morning condensation rate, ~36 mm/hr peak), no frost, no sublimation. Eq. 5.150 routes the dew rate straight to dw_liq_1; the ice-tendency equations remain at zero.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_sdew": 1.0e-5,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_subl": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "dw_liq_1",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0e-5 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "frost_only",
                    "description": "Vapor deposition as frost (q_frost = 5e-6 kg/(m^2*s)) on a sub-freezing surface, no dew, no sublimation. Eq. 5.151 routes the frost rate to dw_ice_1_frost; dw_liq_1 and dw_ice_1_subl stay at zero. Verifies the frost branch is decoupled from the liquid-water branch.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_sdew": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 5.0e-6,
                        "q_subl": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "dw_liq_1",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "time": 0.0, "expected": 5.0e-6 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "sublimation_only",
                    "description": "Sublimation removes ice from the surface (q_subl = 2e-6 kg/(m^2*s)) with no dew or frost. Eq. 5.152 sign-flips the input: dw_ice_1_subl = -q_subl = -2e-6. The other two tendencies stay at zero. Crucial test of the only non-pass-through equation in the component.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_sdew": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_subl": 2.0e-6
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "dw_liq_1",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl",  "time": 0.0, "expected": -2.0e-6 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "dew_plus_frost_morning",
                    "description": "Pre-dawn near-freezing surface: liquid dew co-deposits with frost (q_sdew = 8e-6, q_frost = 3e-6 kg/(m^2*s)), no sublimation. Both ice and liquid tendencies are positive; the sublimation channel stays at zero. Captures the diurnal-transition morning condition where the two condensation branches are simultaneously active.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_sdew": 8.0e-6,
                        "q_frost": 3.0e-6,
                        "q_subl": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "dw_liq_1",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 8.0e-6 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "time": 0.0, "expected": 3.0e-6 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "dew_plus_sublimation",
                    "description": "Sun-warmed surface where existing snow/frost sublimates while new dew condenses (q_sdew = 4e-6, q_subl = 6e-6 kg/(m^2*s)), no fresh frost. dw_liq_1 = 4e-6 (positive — liquid accumulating); dw_ice_1_subl = -6e-6 (negative — ice mass leaving as vapor). The two phase tendencies have opposite signs, exercising the regime where the surface is gaining liquid but losing ice.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_sdew": 4.0e-6,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_subl": 6.0e-6
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "dw_liq_1",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 4.0e-6 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl",  "time": 0.0, "expected": -6.0e-6 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "all_three_active",
                    "description": "All three vapor-exchange channels simultaneously active (q_sdew = 1.5e-5, q_frost = 7e-6, q_subl = 4e-6 kg/(m^2*s)) — a transition-period state where the surface is partly above and partly below freezing within a single tile. Verifies that the three equations are independent: each tendency depends only on its own input, regardless of the others' magnitudes.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_sdew": 1.5e-5,
                        "q_frost": 7.0e-6,
                        "q_subl": 4.0e-6
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "dw_liq_1",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.5e-5 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "time": 0.0, "expected": 7.0e-6 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl",  "time": 0.0, "expected": -4.0e-6 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "negative_q_sdew_evaporation",
                    "description": "Negative q_sdew (= -3e-6 kg/(m^2*s)) — physically a net surface evaporation rather than dew. Eq. 5.150 is sign-preserving, so dw_liq_1 = q_sdew = -3e-6 (negative tendency, liquid is leaving). The upstream MTK component does not clamp the sign of q_sdew; this test pins down that this ESM file inherits the same sign-preserving behavior.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_sdew": -3.0e-6,
                        "q_frost": 0.0,
                        "q_subl": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "dw_liq_1",       "time": 0.0, "expected": -3.0e-6 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-15 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "high_magnitude_storm",
                    "description": "Stress-test of the linear pass-through with high-magnitude inputs (1e-3 kg/(m^2*s) on each — an extreme rime-icing event in the upper bound of physical realism). The exact pass-through and sign-flip behavior must hold at three orders of magnitude above the typical scale, confirming the equations have no hidden non-linearity or saturation.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "q_sdew": 1.0e-3,
                        "q_frost": 1.0e-3,
                        "q_subl": 1.0e-3
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "dw_liq_1",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0e-3 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0e-3 },
                        { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl",  "time": 0.0, "expected": -1.0e-3 }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "sublimation_response_curve",
                    "description": "Sweep the sublimation rate q_subl across the typical CLMU range (0 to 1e-5 kg/(m^2*s)). dw_ice_1_subl traces a straight line from 0 to -1e-5 — visualizing the sign-flip of Eq. 5.152. The other two tendencies stay pinned at zero across the sweep.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "q_sdew": 0.0,
                        "q_frost": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "q_subl",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 1.0e-5, "count": 21, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "dw_ice_subl_vs_q_subl",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "dw_ice_1_subl vs q_subl — straight line through the origin with slope -1, exhibiting Eq. 5.152.",
                            "x": { "variable": "q_subl",        "label": "q_subl (kg/(m^2*s))" },
                            "y": { "variable": "dw_ice_1_subl", "label": "dw_ice_1_subl (kg/(m^2*s))" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "dew_frost_phase_partition",
                    "description": "Joint sweep of dew (q_sdew) and frost (q_frost) rates at fixed zero sublimation. Surfaces the independence of the liquid- and ice-tendency channels: dw_liq_1 depends only on q_sdew, dw_ice_1_frost only on q_frost. Useful as a regression baseline confirming that no cross-coupling has been silently introduced.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "q_subl": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "q_sdew",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 1.0e-5, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "q_frost",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 1.0e-5, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "dw_liq_heatmap",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "dw_liq_1 vs (q_sdew, q_frost) — must vary only along the q_sdew axis.",
                            "x": { "variable": "q_sdew",  "label": "q_sdew (kg/(m^2*s))" },
                            "y": { "variable": "q_frost", "label": "q_frost (kg/(m^2*s))" },
                            "value": { "variable": "dw_liq_1", "reduce": "final" }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "dw_ice_frost_heatmap",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "dw_ice_1_frost vs (q_sdew, q_frost) — must vary only along the q_frost axis.",
                            "x": { "variable": "q_sdew",  "label": "q_sdew (kg/(m^2*s))" },
                            "y": { "variable": "q_frost", "label": "q_frost (kg/(m^2*s))" },
                            "value": { "variable": "dw_ice_1_frost", "reduce": "final" }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
